        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Hey, what do you guys think should be fixed first (other than broken pet taps / stat taps)?</P><P>I find that on most any raid my dots will land.  I have outdamaged many rogues or wizards on some fights (where I've gotten the chance to refresh the longer ones), and came damn close on the shorter ones slapping on some dots and tapping.  Just don't cast EBolt at the start of the fight and die and maybe you'll actually be useful.  Look at people with funeral pyre reporting their damage per tick when stacking dots recently.</P><P>I tagged along on some Ixiblat Fer thing the other day for a cleric.  Yes, taps land.  Yes, even fire based spells can land on him.  Just my pet and dots would have done fine.  But I didn't just do that.  I used some ingenuity and charmed a skelly in the zone along with a chanter's wurm.  Someone parsed the log and my charmed skelly alone had one of the highest damage outputs.</P><P>There are problems with the class, yes, but the way some people do nothing but complain baffles me.  We can do a hell of a lot on raids too if we know what we are doing.  The pets I think should have followed the same progression in gains from 1-49 in the 50s so that they could have some use too.  They should have never been rogues and monks, but stayed warriors.  We aren't situational pet casters like magicians.  I proposed that they return to being warriors.  Maybe that way they can do their damage without getting killed by AoEs cause they can't resist in addition to having less hp than I do.  I asked that their damage still remain the same because as melee damage has increased throughout the game, a warrior nowadays will match the damage of a rogue / monk back when the pets were released.  Is that too much to ask?</P><P>Daedrea Darksoul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
