        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=70579&TOPIC_ID=8751&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Ask+yourself%28about+petition%29&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Coming from the Magician corner, I must agree with potus.</P><P>There is not one issue in this game, not a single one, that out-weighs pets. From the horrible pathing that causes pets to poof (ssra temple, acrylia caverns) to the massive, difficult to resist AoE's.. pet's don't cut it anymore.</P><P>How are the Magician and Necromancer classes supposed to keep up, when their primary source of damage is constantly deemed unusable? I want to know why there are no zones where backstabs randomly hit players. Or, why CHeal doesn't backfire and inst-kill the target. Why doesn't feign death sometimes lock up and keep you from doing anything else? </P><P>The answer is that we aren't part of the holy trinity.  There isn't an endgame encounter that can take place without a warrior tanking, and a cleric healing. That wouldn't be so bad.. but there is literally no situation where you need anyone but a warrior and a cleric. And, no matter how many necromancers and magicians you can fit into a zone, they would never be able to take something like Vyemm without help.</P><P>So, when doing any petition, the first and last thing that should be spoken extensively on is pets. Every single issue pales in comparison, every single one.</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Euri on 12/16/2001  01:41:21<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

