        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/16/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 10:16:46</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2710"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2710')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=70608&TOPIC_ID=8751&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Ask+yourself%28about+petition%29&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I am a little disappointed by the lack of unity on this issue.  I certainly don't agree with everything Potus has said on these boards.  But on this I am definitely in his corner on this, and am a little surprised that more of you are not.</P><P>Abashi and Absor have admitted that the 53 and 56 pets are situational.  This would be fine if we also got general purpose pet upgrades somewhere between 49 and 59.  But we don't.  From levels 1-49 we see a substantial increase in the level, durability, and offensive power in our pets.  After 49, we basically stop growing as a pet class.  The 53 and 56 pets get owned in duels with any of the four level 49 mage pets.  Now, I have no problem with mage pets owning necro pets of equal level--in fact this is needed for game balance.  But to have a mage's 49 pet own my FOCUSED 56 pet is just insulting.</P><P>Finally at 59 we get a true upgrade to the 49 pet.  But the uprade is WAY out of line with the component cost, the cost of obtaining the spell, and the time investment necessary to level to 59.  No, I don't have the 59 pet yet, so how do I know?  Just look at the numbers.  The level 44 pet has a maximum level of 36 and a max hit of 47.  The 49 pet has a maximum level of 41 and hits for a maximum of 55.  So from 44 to 49 we get an upgrade of 5 levels and 8 points in the pet's maximum damage.  The Emissary of Thule has a maximum level of 45 and hits for a max of 59 (less than the 56 pet).  So here we get an upgrade of 4 levels and 4 points in the pet's maximum damage.  Now compare the time required to level from 44 to 49 with the time required to level from 49 to 59, and compare the cost of acquiring the two spells.  (Even if my numbers aren't EXACTLY right, I hope you can still see my argument here.)</P><P>There is a lot of dissatisfaction on these boards and elsewhere with the high end game for necros.  Without getting into any specifics, most of the problem is that our role and abilities as a class change significantly once we hit 50, mostly because the upgrades in our spells fail to keep pace with the increases in hp and offensive capability in the mobs we are fighting.  Our pets are by FAR the most glaring example of this.</P><P>This petition isn't about balance.  It isn't about our role on raids.  All we're asking here is an upgrade to our SINGLE MOST IMPORTANT line of spells that is in line with the time investment made in leveling 51+ and the cost of obtaining the spells.  </P><P>Potus said it best:  <b>There isn't a single issue that outweighs the complete death of pets post 50.</b>  But instead of discussing this issue intelligently we have degenerated into name calling and petty bickering.  I have no problem with people who disagree, in fact some important counterpoints have been made on this thread.  I DO have a problem with people coming on here just to flame Potus, and with those concieted enough to think that the opinion of people below 60 and/or not in an uberguild somehow don't count.</P><P>Potus is making a serious effort here to help our class.  And if we can't even discuss this issue maturely and constructively, don't expect any changes to be made.</P><P>Nahaz Millithor<BR>57 Defiler, Seekers of Unity<BR>Solusek Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
